    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Many thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Letter of oct<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 26<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0529">Barbour</title>
                    </bibl> will be
                    acceptable in any form: the little edition may come piece meal &amp; beg the
                    favor of <persName ref="pe0018">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Jackson</persName> to frank it.</p>
                <p>Let me beg you w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> enquire if <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0093">Gordon’s maps in Blaeu’s atlas</title>
                    </bibl> is to
                    be had &amp; at what price. I mean the edition of 1662 with melvin’s topographie
                    in it.</p>
                <p>Also <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0094">sacheverels voy. to Iona a small
                                oct<hi rend="superscript">vo</hi>
                        </title>
                    </bibl>.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> had best
                    keep his materials till he has completed his collection. I urge him to visit
                    every isle personally: &amp; shall soon send him a sketch of the <unclear reason="illegible">Imber</unclear>
                </p>
                <p>I imagine <persName ref="pe0022">Doctor Ramsay</persName> will not be worse for
                    the loss of <persName ref="pe0603">his father</persName> who I hear was a
                    strange fellow.</p>
                <p>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> favor is just come.
                    &amp; many thanks for the sheet which I rejoice to see. Whatever else you send
                    will be most welcome.</p>
                <p>Had you my Letter to <persName ref="pe0100">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Freebairn of Ilay</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Dear Sir <lb/>in much haste y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232"/>Tho. Pennant</signed>
                </closer>

                <dateline>Nov<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>
                    1773.</dateline>

                <postscript>
                    <p> Pray is it true that <persName ref="pe0073">the great Doctor
                            Johnson</persName> was weather bound in <placeName ref="pl0715">Skie</placeName>. </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
